      <bioghist id="aspace_92a87cd11debbbba6469f388554f5441">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Yale Institute of Sacred Music is an interdisciplinary graduate center for the study and practice of sacred music.  The Institute's primary mission is to music students whose vocation is to conduct, play, and sing for the worshiping assembly, and who have a keen interest in the religious and theological contexts of the sacred music they perform.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_4eb67669bb60ec4fed613ec4462e4ecc">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>Some records in this finding aid have been redacted, as they include student names, donor names, and other restricted data. These records will not appear in the published finding aid.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
